The paper discusses the use of image-based modeling and laser scanning for large-scale architectural scene reconstruction, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and graphics (cs.GR) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the automatic planning of laser scanning locations, which involves robotics (cs.RO) and machine learning (cs.AI) techniques. Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed pipeline using experimental data, which involves multimedia (cs.MM) analysis and processing.
